               I have the honour of informing you that the Emperor, my august Sovereign, wishing to give you a particular sign of his esteem and benevolence, has just, at my suggestion, conferred on you the Knight's Cross of his Imperial Order of the Legion of Honour. It has been very pleasing for me to call down on you this mark of distinction, which you have earned by the services you have rendered to various French scientific establishments;

M was made an honorary member of the Imperial Zoological Society of Acclimatization (Société Impériale Zoologique d'Acclimatation), Paris, in 1861, and a correspondent of the Museum of Natural History (Muséum d'Histoire Naturelle), Paris in 1862.
                and I hasten to send you the diploma and the insignia that are destined for you. With my sincere congratulations, Sir, accept this expression of my highest respect.
